        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Barcelona Venzl<hi rend="sup">a</hi></placeName> <date>July 24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee> Esqr.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philad P<hi rend="sup">a</hi>.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. Sir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">There being so very few occurrences of this nature in this<lb/> part of the world&#44; adding thereto your accustomed desire of obtaining<lb/> information concerning our people&#44; has quite induced me to take<lb/> the liberty to encroach on your precious moments&#44; with the object of<lb/> calling your attention to the late &#38; agreeable occurrences&#44; which I trust<lb/> will prove interesting to those interested in the progress of the Jews<lb/> even amidst the most <sic>bigotted</sic> sect of christianity.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">We have often performed the ceremony of <add>Hebrew</add> in the families<lb/> of <persName>Messrs. is. Baiz</persName>&#44; <persName>M. H. Baiz</persName>&#44; <persName>Is. Valencia</persName>&#44; <persName>Is. L Lindo</persName>&#44; <persName>A. H. Moron</persName>&#44;<lb/> all of whom possess a numerous family &#38; resident of this place<lb/> The said ceremonies having been expected by <persName>Messrs. Is. Sass</persName> of <placeName>St Thos.</placeName><lb/> &#38; <persName>M F. Ricardo</persName> of <placeName>Curacao</placeName>&#44; both <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Our &#8220;progress&#8221; has been such&#44; that we were lately obliged<lb/> to open a new <add>&#63;</add>olio entitled &#8220;Marriages&#8221; where two young cou&#45;<lb/>ples were enlisted &#38; another soon to follow.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Names of the Marr<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. Couples&#58; in <date>Feby</date> last&#44; <persName>Jb. Levy Maduro</persName> to <persName>Miss Jud.</persName><lb/> <persName>Jesn. Lindo</persName>&#59; on the <date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst&#44; <persName>Michael Perrso</persName> to <persName>Miss Reb. Sasso.</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">For want of a better&#44; I was honoured with the task of <add>Hebrew</add> which<lb/> was performed according to our rites&#44; <persName>Mr. M. H. Buiz</persName> as V. C of the <placeName>U. S. A.</placeName><lb/> certifying to the <sic>legallity</sic> of the said act. The attendance of the<lb/> natives&#44; including the civil Authorities&#44; were numerous in both<lb/> cases &#38; feel proud to add that the solemnity of the act has created<lb/> some sensations among the Goyims.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The families &#38; Individuals residing here are&#58; <persName>Is. Baiz</persName> &#38; family</p>
			<p rend="align(right)">over</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><persName>Is. Valencia</persName> &#38; family&#44; <persName>M. H. Baiz</persName> &#38; family&#59; <persName>Is. Jes. Lindo</persName> &#38; family&#59; <persName>A. H.<lb/> Moron</persName> &#38; family&#59; <persName>Michl. Perrso</persName> &#38; lady&#59; <persName>Abm. Jes Lindo</persName>&#44; <persName>Danl Delima</persName>.<lb/> &#40;to be married to <persName>Miss Sar. Valencia</persName>&#41; <persName>Josiah L. Henriguez</persName>&#44; <persName>Mordy R. Caprilles</persName><lb/> &#38; myself beside a son of <persName>Mr. M H Baiz</persName> who is already over 13 years.&#44;&#8212;you<lb/> will therefore observe that we complete full Minyan&#44; even<lb/> for <date>Kipur</date>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Should you deem these Items worthy of occupying a space<lb/> in your valuable journal&#44; I will feel most proud of having added to<lb/> your gen<hi rend="sup">l</hi>. Stock. &#160;&#160;Meanwhile I subscribe myself</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">Revd. Sir&#33; Your most Ob<hi rend="sup">t</hi>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Sam Piza</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>The</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p>politely recommended to <persName>Mr. Gershom Nathan</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>143 Canal St.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(5)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">New York</hi></placeName></p>
          
